Lagos has continues as the epicentre of coronavirus pandemic in Nigeria as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control late on Thursday confirmed 13 new cases in Nigeria’s economic hub. Announcing the new development on its Twitter handle, NCDC said Delta State had one new case, bringing the total number of confirmed cases in Nigeria to 288. In addition, the number of discharged patients has moved to 51 from 44 as at Wednesday.The number of deaths increased by one, bringing the total number of casualties to seven. The Tweet reads: Fourteen new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria: 13 in Lagos and 1 in Delta State As at 09:30 pm 9th April there are 288 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Fifty-one have been discharged with seven deaths.  https://t.co/DuP2SGUiTy As at 09:30 pm 9th April, there are288 confirmed cases51 discharged7 deaths For more info-https://t.co/zQrpNeOfet Lagos- 158FCT- 54Osun- 20Edo- 12Oyo- 11Bauchi- 6Akwa Ibom- 5Ogun- 4Kaduna- 5Enugu- 2Ekiti- 2Rivers-2Kwara- 2Delta- 2Benue- 1Ondo- 1Katsina-1 ABUJA - The coronavirus pandemic continued its spread in Nigeria with 16 new confirmed cases on Tuesday as announced by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). First the time since the end of first case was announced in Nigeria in February the disease has reached Katsina with one confirmed… April 7, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - Ten new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria; seven in Lagos and three in the FCT, according to the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC).Also, the NCDC said 11 more cases have been discharged bringing the total number of discharged cases to 20. The number of… April 2, 2020 In "News" AbUJA - Six new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria: 2 in Kwara, 2 in Edo, 1 in Rivers and 1 in the FCT, according to the Nigeria Centre for Disease control (NCDC). As at 09:30 pm 6th April there are 238 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in… April 6, 2020 In "News"